         <div type="translation">
            <p>Artemon son of Adrastos the son of Dionysios the son of Dinomachos dedicated the six columns at his own expense to the People, with their capitals</p>
         </div>
         <div type="commentary">
            <p>These four columns are from a group of six dedicated by Artemon. Another two survive from the 14 dedicated by Nestor and Zenon, <ref type="inscription" n="1111" target="050205.xml"/>, (=Mendel 173). For further column dedications from the Hadrianic Baths see <ref type="iAph" target=".xml"/> (=Boulanger B Page 23 no. 29), and <ref type="inscription" n="1112" target="050003.xml"/> (=84.64).</p>
         </div>
